Description: Solebit takes a non-behavioral approach to detecting and preventing APTs and zero-day attacks.
Full Description: Solebit provides the fastest, most accurate and cost-effective approach for the identification and prevention of zero-day malware and unknown threats. SoleGATE is the disruptive cyber protection software platform by Solebit, challenging the norms of currently available technologies that rely on slow, costly and mostly outdated, ineffective methods of sandboxing, signatures and behavioral inspection. The solution is powered by DvC™ (data vs. code), a patented, real-time, signature-less engine. DvC assumes that there is no legitimate reason for executable code to be present in any data file. As such, it does not rely on heuristics or behaviors (which are core limitations of competing technologies), and definitively identifies and terminates any instance of malicious code such as hidden CPU instructions,  encrypted and polymorphic payloads, shellcodes and other commands typically buried in data file. DvC also accurately identifies an blocks malicious active content using advanced flow analysis, de-obfuscation techniques and deep content evaluation, to reveal threat intent within any inbound data file covering machine, operating system and application levels, thereby rendering such sandbox evading attacks harmless to the enterprise. Solebit was founded in 2014 by a team of world-class cybersecurity experts, all graduates of the elite technology units in the Israel Defense Forces with years of experience in offensive and defensive security. It counts a variety of leading global financial organizations, tech, defense contractors, security vendors, cloud and telecom service providers as active customers. For more information, please visit solebit.io
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Industry Groups: Consumer Electronics, Hardware, Information Technology, Other, Privacy and Security, Software
Founders: Boris Vanyberg, Meni Farjon, Yossi Sara

Plasma Activated Water is produced by making use of water, air and electricity. Ambient air is brought into the plasma phase with electrical energy and plasma activated air is brought into contact with water. Reactive oxygen and nitrogen are dissolved into the water creating Plasma Activated Water. The process of treating water with plasma is copied out of nature. When lightning strikes during a thunderstorm, rain and water are treated with plasma. It is one of nature's ways to fixate nitrogen in the form of nitrate, the most important fertilizer for plants and crops.

Description: Index is a genetic food system traceability solutions provider specializing in source-of-origin traceability and identity preservation.
Full Description: Index Biosystems is a genetic food system traceability solutions provider specializing in source-of-origin traceability and identity preservation. By guaranteeing sub-population level source-of-origin identification, we empower a TraceForward approach to traceability.  Index’s core technology involves inserting an inert genetic construct into food system products - a Nuclid™. This includes inputs, feed, seed, food and additives. Identification can be accurately achieved within a few hours independent of packaging (even in co-mingled or transformed products), greatly reducing the impacts of any recall. Our solution works in concert with legacy systems and expands the scope of what is traceable - from seed to waste, including post-digestion.  Because this solution provides simple identification, there are many use-cases. Some use cases that we’ve identified include: Recall scope reduction Operational insights GMO identification Fraud identification Feed and seed security IP tracking Food system certification Waste tracking

Description: Proteins, Animal Feed, Nutrition, Biotechnology, CleanTech, AgTech, Agriculture, Green Energy, Sustainability, Clean Energy
Full Description: Problem >>The production of sunflower oil produces approx. 60% meal (practically waste), which contains high-quality proteins. Oil can only be produced to the extent that this waste can be re-housed. Animal feed from soy meal, rainforest is cleared for it.   Product >> Makes the waste 100% usable; high protein is produced, for animal feed (protein over 46%), so that soybean meal can be displaced from the market by sunflower (protection of rainforest); an energy source is produced from the remaining fibre content;   Sales channels & promotion >> We grant licences for the patented process to existing millers. These pay an amount per tonne. The licences are distributed through sales agents (target group: seed and feed traders). In addition, direct approach to mills. Construction of own plant (60,000 t annual capacity). Results >> In the calculated normal case (for annual capacity of a plant in Germany of 240,000 t), the mix of the products HiProSUN I, HiProSUN II and HiProSUN III results in a net profit of 57% and an EBITDA of 51%.

Canaries have been extensively used in research to study neurogenesis, or the birth of new neurons in the adult brain, and also for basic research in order to understand how songbirds encode and produce song. Thus, canaries have served as model species for discovering how the vertebrate brain learns, consolidates memories, and recalls coordinated motor movements.  This is a good analogy for Neural networks where backpropagation represents learning, final weights represent consolidated memories, and model inference represents recalling motor movements. Description: ARED is a infrastructure as a service company to help grow the digital economy in Africa.
Full Description: ARED Group Inc was founded in August 2020, we are building a distributed cloud infrastructure as a service company headquartered in the USA with subsidies in Rwanda, Uganda, and Nigeria. ARED started as a Research Lab in 2013, our goal was to help bridge the digital divide that affects over 4 billion people across the world. Most of the investment in the digital divide is focused on bandwidth, yet most of the storage and computing power is controlled by 3 main companies and centralized infrastructure is very expensive. Also, most of the smartphones in developing countries are low-end smartphones with low internal memory and low processing power that accentuate the digital divide. Finally, lack of energy access is a huge problem, if you do not have electricity at home you cannot charge your phone and use it the way you want, also building storage and computing power solution require energy that is why at ARED we use renewable energy.  To solve this digital divide, ARED developed a mini-server platform to store digital applications closer to the users and minimize the cost of the internet, and we developed a solar kiosk platform to power the technology but also provide additional services such as phone charging to become a one-stop-shop platform.  We spent 6 years developing the technology, and in 2020 we started piloting our technology in 6 African countries with local partners (Rwanda, Uganda, Nigeria, Ethiopia, Burkinafaso, and Ivory Coast).  ARED mission is simple, eliminate the digital divide across the world by building a distributed infrastructure closer to the users to minimize the digital access for users.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Industry Groups: Hardware, Internet Services, Mobile, Real Estate, Software, Sustainability

Description: DoorSpace is a SaaS Platform transforming the way healthcare organizations retain and develop their clinical talent
Full Description: DoorSpace is transforming the way healthcare organizations retain and develop clinical talent. We have an innovative solution that flips the script on the usual question “what makes people leave?”, and instead asks “what makes people stay?”.  We’ve built a platform specifically designed to make it easier for organizations to create a workplace where people want to stay.  With our solution, healthcare organizations are better able to:  * know your people, and build strong relationships with them  * Reduce friction/frustration in clinician’s workflow by eliminating wasteful administrative tasks * support your people more effectively in their career development ** All while dramatically reducing the amount of time your clinicians and your administrative team is spending on manual data entry and paper pushing. **  How We Do It:  DoorSpace’s SaaS platform provides an intelligent data management system, enabling clinicians and their employers to collaborate, manage and maintain mission-critical personnel data.  DoorSpace provides a “single source of truth” that is updated in real-time across the organization each time an employee’s data file changes. We provide organizations with the workforce data they need to make data-driven decisions, and we reduce the time high-value talent is spending on low-value administrative tasks.  The immediate value DoorSpace provides our customers is that we clean up a lot of back office "clutter", automating the ongoing organization and maintenance of personnel data and documents.  The long term value DoorSpace provides to healthcare leaders is transparency across their workforce with real-time reporting and superior data accuracy, enabling better, faster decisions.  Specific Pain Points We Address:    * Clinicians and administrators wasting valuable time pushing paper and manually moving data from one silo’d system to another;    * Healthcare leaders wait months to get reports on the state of their workforce, delaying the resolution of serious problems until after impacted clinicians have quit;    * Inability to quickly identify clinician’s strengths and weaknesses to ensure strengths are leveraged while bolstering weaknesses with the right training;    * Delays that are weeks and often months long in getting things done - from placing a new clinician to billing insurance companies and every step along the way, back office inefficiencies      are costing organizations time and money they can’t afford to spend;   * Employers need to both ramp up recruiting to keep staff - ratios, and they need to increase investment in retention with limited resources;    * Growing turnover and no insights or clear strategic retention plan beyond paying clinicians more money;   * Growing frustration among clinicians, especially doctors and nurses, which has led to an increase in medical errors, nurse strikes, turnover, and disengagement from patient care work;

Description: Flextrapower is a remote-monitoring company powered by graphene technology.
Full Description: Flextrapower is a remote monitoring company powered by graphene technology, a disruptive material with unique properties that allow for ground-breaking biomedical applications. Graphene is stronger than steel, yet incredibly lightweight and flexible. It is electrically and thermally conductive but also transparent. It’s one million times thinner than the diameter of a single human hair.  Our team has developed and patented a method to seamlessly embed graphene sensors into flexible materials, like clothing. This method enables us to develop state-of-the-art remote monitoring products that advance health outcomes and improve patient care.  Currently, Flextrapower has developed a smart insole that detects diabetic foot ulcers, an EMG-integrated smart shirt, and a COVID-19 mask featuring a layer of graphene.

In addition, the company buys vehicles from consumers and sells them to dealers through auto auctions. Founded by Alon, a former software engineer with a history of entrepreneurial ventures, Clutch secured funding a few months after its inception. Clutch also operates BuyBids.com, a subsidiary B2B SaaS platform designed to serve both auto brokers and dealers. BuyBids provides instant buy bids for customer trade-ins, allowing brokers to make a spread on the deal. For dealers, it offers a streamlined way to offload unwanted trade-ins. This platform serves as a tool for brokers and dealers to earn additional revenue and as a channel for Clutch to acquire inventory without direct consumer marketing. The company aims to simplify the car buying and selling process, offering a streamlined experience for both consumers and dealers.

Description: SaaS, B2B, Remote communication, Virtual collaboration, AI, NLP, Live data
Full Description: Knock Technology creates and operates SaaS products for remote work productivity. The company's first product is noc™ - a video communication tool, scientifically designed to minimise the cognitive effort of context-switching between tasks and calls. By minimising the cognitive load on the human brain, users are able to communicate more naturally whilst maintaining focus on their current task. This results in reduced mental exhaustion ("Zoom fatigue"), fewer incidences of miscommunication, improved productivity, innovation, and staff retention. The product also uses natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) algorithms to summarise conversational content and deliver live, unbiased operational data to business leaders. After a call, the NLP transcript is compressed by the AI into a bullet-pointed summary of the conversation. For larger companies, the AI compresses all conversation data to present a live operational dashboard to senior leadership, helping them make more informed decisions. The company has been awarded grant funding by the EU's Regional Development Fund and Innovate UK's Transformative Technologies Fund for research into the effects of remote communication on mental health, productivity and innovation, as well as its contribution towards net zero carbon emissions by reducing the demand for travel. The product was created by thought-leading user experience designers, MBA graduates and PhD neuroscientists from Cranfield University, The University of Bristol and University College London to fill a gap in the remote comms market for instant, casual communication with distant colleagues. It uses a unique peer-to-peer network architecture that bypasses data centres for a faster, clearer and more energy-efficient connection.

Description: Like Uber but with Teslas.
Full Description: Offering on-demand, eco-friendly rides in Nashville, TN. To ensure healthy earth for future generations, our goal is to get you safely from point A to point B while removing gas transportation from the equation. That is why our fleet is made of 100% electric vehicles, so you don't have to choose between the planet and convenience. Currently, our fleet consists of Teslas. We look forward to expanding our car options as more car companies begin to produce 100% electric vehicles.
Industry Groups: Transportation

Description: Tendo is a technology company that provides economical solutions for flow rate and pressure measurements.
Full Description: Tendo is an industrial technology company that uses novel elastic filament velocimetry technology. Their miniature sensor can detect low flow rates with precision and measure temperature, all at a price point. Tendo aims to leverage advancements and expertise in high-fidelity flow measurements to dramatically improve flow sensing fidelity at a significantly lower cost.
Industry Groups: Science and Engineering
Founders: Clayton Byers, Marcus Hultmark, MATT FU, YUYANG FAN
Top 5 Investors: National Science Foundation, NJEDA, True Capital Management, Tyche, Rhapsody Venture Partners
